# Git And PR Workflow

- Never start new work from local `main`.
- Create branches from `origin/main` with `make start-branch BRANCH=fix/my-change` or `git fetch origin && git switch -c <branch> --track origin/main`.
- Treat local `main` as sync-only. Do not commit or push feature work from it.
- Before opening or updating a PR, run `make pr-ready`.
- When using GitHub CLI, create PRs with `gh pr create --body-file scripts/governance/pr_body_template.md`.
- Do not replace the PR body with ad hoc text that drops the required Change Ledger sections.
- For **end-to-end governed delivery** (GitHub `main` → staging → production), follow `.cursor/rules/governed-release-kasa.mdc` (CI proof, HTTP/version checks, lockfile remediation, `gh` rate-limit hygiene).
